# Game Code Patterns

## File roles

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `entities/Table.ts` | Play bounds, wall static group, goal zones |
| `entities/Stick.ts` | Container rod + pawns, slide/rotate, `syncPhysics()` |
| `entities/Ball.ts` | Arcade image, bounce/drag from config |
| `systems/StickInputController.ts` | Keyboard columns → `setSlideTarget()` |
| `scenes/Game.ts` | Spawn all, colliders, `update()` loop |

## Stick physics

Pawns use invisible `StaticGroup` bodies. Each frame after move/rotate:

```ts
body.setPosition(worldX, worldY);
body.refreshBody();
```

Ball collides with `table.walls` and shared `pawnGroup`.

## Adding a stick feature

1. State + method on `Stick` (e.g. `setRodRotation`)
2. Input wiring in new or existing system class
3. Call `stick.update(delta)` from `Game.update` for player sticks
4. Never skip `syncPhysics()` after transform changes

## Scene bootstrap order

`generateTextures()` → `Table` → `pawnGroup` → sticks → `Ball` → colliders → input → `EventBus.emit`
